[White "Introduction"]
[Black "Course Introduction"]
[Result "*"]

{ Introduction   Hello! Welcome to this course, wherein we will be presenting a repertoire for Black against the Spanish Game or Ruy Lopez.  Our main variation of choice will be the Open Variation, which arises after  1.e4  e5  2.Nf3  Nc6  3.Bb5  a6  4.Ba4  Nf6  and now  5.O-O  Nxe4  . White's deviations on moves 4 and 5 will also be covered.  We have designed it from the ground up to be both practical and ambitious. To this end, theImportant lines feature was used, which you can enable in the course options tab. We have also included aQuickstarter with 10 must-know lines designed to get you playing the Open Spanish in no time.  We've tried our best to strike a fine balance between making a repertoire playable all the way up to the GM level while still making it accessible to club players. We made full use of the latest versions of Stockfish and Leela running on superfast cloud servers, ensuring all the analysis presented is cutting-edge. Moreover, we've proposed a whole array of novelties that are likely to surprise your opponents and give you the upper hand in a practical game. For added flexibility, we give two independent repertoires versus the absolute mainlines - check out theRepertoire outline section for all the details!  After going through the various theoretical chapters, you can test your understanding of key nuances and tactical sequences using theMemory markers andTactical puzzes chapters, respectively. To improve your general understanding of the Open Spanish, we included a standalone chapter onpositional and tactical themes that crop up time and time again in this opening. There are also 19model games showcasing these and other themes in action.  Finally, you can count on a high support level. We will promptly answer any questions you have and regularly update the course with new theoretical developments.   That's all for the intro, we hope you enjoy the course and have great success with this repertoire! }
