[White "Positional and Tactical Themes"]
[Black "Chapter Introduction"]
[Result "*"]

{ Positional and Tactical themes In this chapter, we will look at some typical positional and tactical themes which I feel are important for understanding the basics of the Open Variation. Obviously, this is far from a comprehensive list, and if you're experienced in this variation, you doubtless are already familiar with most or all of these. The idea is to give some context to readers who may be completely new to the lines that are covered in this course.  Understanding what both sides are trying to accomplish is important to get a full understanding of the intricacies of the Open Spanish. As such, we present common themes for both White and Black. We start out with themes for Black followed by ones from White's point of view. }
