[SetUp "1"]

15... a5
{ Here, we have a similar structure to the previous line, but with ... c7-c5 difficult to achieve in a good way. Black therefore opts for another method of counterplay. Mikhalevski explains that the text gains space on the Queenside while keeping the ...c5 push in reserve. }
16. Rec3 Rc8 { Defending c7 and potentially supporting a ...c5 break. } 17. Nf3
a4 18. Bc2 g6 { Blunting the c2 Bishop along the long diagonal. } 19. Bd3 b4
{ Black has excellent counterplay on the queenside. } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Positional and Tactical Themes"]
[Black "The ...f6 break #1 | Black"]
