Bxb3 22. Rd6 h5
{ Black's position is somewhat awkward in that he lacks useful moves to make while White rounds up the c5 and a6 pawns. With the text, he gains space and creates luft for his King. Black is likely to end up in an endgame a pawn down, but with White unable to make any progress. }
23. Ra5 Be6 24. Rxc5 a5
{ Giving up the pawn is advisable here, as capturing it gives us access to the b8 square for our Rook. }
25. Nxa5 Rfb8 26. Rd2 h4
{ White is a pawn up, but his pieces are so tangled up that there is no progress to be made here. }
