{ 18...Nxb2  19.Bxd5  is also possible. Instead, Black simply connects his pawns and defends  d5  .  The b2 pawn is now genuinely threatened. White may take on c4, after which we can take back with the b-pawn and use the half-open b-file. Otherwise, the second player can look to centralize his Rooks, and may eventually play for ...c5. }
