16... Ne5
{ A natural follow-up, taking advantage of the fact that Nxe5 is impossible. Black has to act swiftly as Bg5 was coming. }
17. Be3 { White is best advised to keep developing. } 17... Nxf3+ 18. Qxf3 Qxf3
19. gxf3 Rxf3
{ With a second pawn in the bag and very active pieces, Black is doing well and has had good results in practice. ...Bh3 and ...g6 are natural follow-ups. If White's knight heads to g3, ...h5-h4 is often a good idea. }
