{ is the way to go with the knight on e4 as the c5 pawn needs attention.   17...Nbd4  while playable is not as strong as the text due to  18.Nxd4  Nxd4  19.Be3  a5  20.Nxc5!  This tactical resource was not available in the 16.Nc4 variation and is the reason we place our queen on b6. }
18. Be3 a5
{ Liberates the rook from the defense of the a-pawn with a solid position. White can land the knight on d6 but it won't yield the first player anything of value.   For example  19.Nd6  Nxd6  20.exd6  Rfd8  21.d7  Nf8  The pawn made it all the way to d7 but that's as far as it'll go. It's now essentially a target.  22.Rd5  Qe6  23.Rad1  Ra7  24.Bxc5  Bxc5  25.Rxc5  Rdxd7  26.Re1  Qb6=  with full equality. }
