Be6 9. Nbd2 Be7 10. c3 O-O 11. Re1
{ This line can arise from a few different move orders, including 9.Re1 and 9.c3 Be7 10.Re1. }
11... Nc5
{ Black finally moves his Knight away from e4.   Note that  11...f5?  12.exf6  Nxf6??  13.Rxe6  is not possible for Black. }
12. Bc2
{ This is the less dangerous of the two principal moves available to White. }
12... d4
{ This thematic break tends to ensure a good game for Black. Play could continue as follows. }
13. cxd4 Nxd4 14. Nxd4 Qxd4 15. Nf3 Qxd1 16. Rxd1 Rad8
{ Black has a satisfactory endgame. At some point, he may expand on the queenside with ...c7-c5 and try to put his majority to good use. }
