1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. O-O Nxe4 6. d4 b5 7. Bb3 d5 8. dxe5
Be6 9. Nbd2 Be7 10. c3 O-O 11. Qe2
{ A different way of attacking the Knight on e4. Once again, it's time to move the Knight away, since ...f5 doesn't work. }
11... Nc5 12. Bc2 d4 { As so often, this break solves Black's problems. } *

