1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. O-O Nxe4 6. d4 b5 7. Bb3 d5 8. dxe5
Be6 9. Nbd2 Be7 10. c3 O-O 11. Qe2 Nc5 12. Nd4 Qd7 13. Bc2
{ White preserves his Bishop. } 13... Bg4
{ Black annoys the White Queen, while preparing to swing this Bishop around to h5 and g6 and clearing e6 for another piece. }
14. Qe3 Nxd4 15. cxd4 Ne6
{ We're using our Knight to blockade the e5 pawn, while also clearing the way for the ...c5 break. }
16. h3 Bh5 17. f4
{ White is threatening to run Black over with g4 and f5, but we have a good reply. }
17... f5
{ White's Kingside play is blocked, and in fact, he has to be careful to avoid being worse, as ...c5 is coming. }
