1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. O-O Nxe4 6. d4 b5 7. Bb3 d5 8. dxe5
Be6 9. Nbd2 Be7 10. c3 O-O 11. Bc2 f5 12. Nd4 Nxd4 13. cxd4 Qd7 14. Nb3 a5
{ Intending to kick the Knight with ...a4. Note that White cannot play a4 himself, as that pawn would hang. }
15. f3 a4 16. fxe4 axb3 17. Bxb3 fxe4
{ Black has equalized. The pawn structure is a little unusual, with both sides having protected passed e-pawns. You could argue that White's blockade is slightly easier to challenge than Black's on e6. ...c5 is very much still in the picture, although Black may also content himself with the solid ...c6. }
