1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. O-O Nxe4 6. d4 b5 7. Bb3 d5 8. dxe5
Be6 9. Nbd2 Be7 10. c3 O-O 11. Bc2 f5 12. exf6
{ This is the second most popular move, after 12.Nb3. White avoids the closed structure that would arise there, and instead opts to open the position. This gives Black the half-open f-file, but his position is a bit looser. }
12... Nxf6 13. Ng5
{ White makes an immediate threat, but we have a good reply. } 13... Bg4 14. f3
Bd7
{ We have induced the weakening move f2-f3, which also deprives the g5 Knight of a retreat square, leaving it somewhat stranded. Black is better. }
