{ This is another important move. Black prepares both ...Bd6 which can be followed up with ...Be4 if the Queen goes to b7 and ...Rg6, should the Queen retreat to g3. We are two pawns down, but Black's pieces are so active and White's Queen so vulnerable that the first player already has to be very careful not to end up in trouble. }
