1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. c3
{ This is a logical enough move, but it encounters the problem of being premature. Black has more than one way of obtaining slightly preferable chances. }
5... Nxe4
{ 5...b5  is also possible, but why not play the thematic Open Spanish move? It's especially strong here, as White has yet to castle, and has instead played c2-c3; of debatable value here. }
6. Qe2 Nc5 { We've seen this motif of attacking the Bishop before. } 7. Bxc6
dxc6 8. d4 Ne6 9. Nxe5 Bd6
{ Black has an even better version of the Re1 Open Spanish positions, as White's Queen seems misplaced on e2. }
