10. Rd1
{ This is a common move. Now, we'll get to see Black's ideal scheme of development. }
10... Re8 11. Nbd2 h6
{ This isn't forced, but it's worthwhile to play this at some stage to stop Ng5. }
12. Nf1 { White brings his Knight around to g3. } 12... Bd6
{ This improves the Bishop slightly, unveils the Rook on e8, and covers the e5 pawn in preparation for our next move. }
13. Ng3 Na5 14. Bc2 c5
{ Black has a nice space advantage and should be better. The a5-Knight tends to drop back to c6, and he can create play with either ...c4 or ...d4. }
