{ How can Black ensure he's not run over on the kingside? } 13... Qd7
{ This introduces the idea of ...Bg4, but also generally takes further control over the light squares, which is useful in a structure where f4-f5 is one of White's major ideas. It also allows for Bc2 to be met with ...Bf5 in the future. }
14. Bg5 Bg4 15. Qh4 Bc5
{ Exchanging these Bishops is also okay, but Black reasons that the g5 Bishop is now hitting air, whereas c5 is a nice square for his own piece. }
16. Rae1 O-O
{ It is now safe to castle, as the Bc2 idea no longer carries so much weight, due to: }
17. Bc2 Bf5
{ Black has neutralized White's kingside pressure and is completely fine. Black can now look to activate his Rooks and expand on the Queenside at some point. }
