{ Black must seek active counterplay, and so he puts his own pawn majority to use. }
24. f6 Bd8
{ 24...gxf6?  25.Bh6  is good for White, who has the plan of Qe1-g3+. } 25. Be3
{ White uses the pin to win the d4 pawn. } 25... gxf6
{ This pawn is safe to capture now. } 26. --
{ Were White to play  26.Bh6  here, Black's extra tempo of...Bd8 would help him significantly, as the Queen now defends the seventh rank. }
