{ We have the bishop pair but every piece but our knight is at home. How do we start putting pressure on our opponent? }
13... h5
{ This is a nice idea. The point is to keep the King in the centre, and activate the h8 Rook by playing ...h4 and ...Rh5. If you've studied the Berlin, you may well have come across this idea. Black has a superior version of the Berlin here, as White lacks the initiative he would normally have, and Black maintains castling rights. }
14. h3 h4 15. Ne3 { The e5-pawn is weak. } *

